{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Cd27UD1hCJFBJmu6S4Fjv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Review complete. This is a clean, correctly-scoped deletion.\n\n## Verification performed (independent of the description)\n\n- `git status --short` / `git diff` confirm the working tree contains exactly one change: deletion of `web-react-ts/src/components/pie-chart/CustomLabel.tsx` (41 lines, a `<g>`/`<text>` SVG label component for a pie chart).\n- `grep -rni \"customlabel\" web-react-ts/src` → zero hits (including the file itself, now gone).\n- `grep -rni \"pie-chart\" web-react-ts/src` → zero hits (no relative-path imports, no barrel re-exports, no dynamic `import()`/`require()` strings).\n- No test file (`*.test.tsx`, snapshot, etc.) anywhere under `web-react-ts/src` references `CustomLabel` or `pie-chart`.\n- Repo-wide grep (outside `web-react-ts/src` too) for `customlabel` / `pie-chart` → only two non-code hits, both documentation, not importers:\n  - `web-react-ts/kb/02-design-system.md:88` — \"Charts | Keep `recharts` (`components/ChurchGraph`, `components/pie-chart`)\"\n  - `.claude/commands/new-component.md:41` — lists `pie-chart/` as an example charts folder.\n\nNo issues found with the deletion itself.\n\n## Should Fix\n\n- `web-react-ts/src/components/pie-chart/CustomLegend.tsx` and `web-react-ts/src/components/pie-chart/PieChart.css` — now fully orphaned. `grep -rn \"CustomLegend\" web-react-ts/src` returns only the component's own file (its type declaration and export), and `PieChart.css` is imported only by `CustomLegend.tsx`. With `CustomLabel.tsx` gone, the entire `pie-chart/` directory is dead code. Recommend a follow-up ticket to delete `CustomLegend.tsx` and `PieChart.css` together (they were never imported by this diff, so out of scope for SYN-204, but should not be left behind). Note also that `CustomLegend.tsx` is still on Bootstrap utility classes (`d-flex`, `justify-content-between`, `badge`, `badge-pill`, `bg-dark`) — another reason it shouldn't linger as an untouched, unreachable Bootstrap island; better to delete than migrate a component with no callers.\n\n## Consider\n\n- `web-react-ts/kb/02-design-system.md:88` lists `components/pie-chart` as a chart component to \"keep\" alongside `ChurchGraph`. This is now stale/incorrect once the directory is fully removed — worth a one-line KB update in the same follow-up ticket that removes `CustomLegend.tsx`/`PieChart.css`, per CLAUDE.md's guidance to flag KB/code discrepancies.\n- `.claude/commands/new-component.md:41` also cites `pie-chart/` as an example folder; low priority, but same stale reference once the directory is gone.\n\n## Tests\n\nNo test file existed for `CustomLabel.tsx` (confirmed via the searches above), so there is no test to delete or update alongside this change. This falls under the \"no unit-testable surface\" carve-out for a pure deletion of an already-untested, unreferenced component — there's no behavior left to characterize. `tsc --noEmit`, `npm run build`, and `npm run test:run` passing (with the pre-existing, pre-change `createApolloClient.test.tsx` failure) as reported is adequate verification for a deletion-only change; I did not re-run them myself since the diff contains no logic to re-verify beyond what's already been confirmed.\n\n**Bottom line:** the deletion is safe and minimal exactly as described. Recommend opening a fast-follow ticket for `CustomLegend.tsx` + `PieChart.css` (and the two KB/doc mentions) before closing out SYN-204's parent cleanup, but that is not a blocker for this PR."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":687,"cache_read_input_tokens":24030,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":687,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_i